<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,306,1106]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swallen" authorityYear="1966" box="[151,344,306,331]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laxa">
<emphasis box="[151,344,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Eriochrysis laxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beauvois" authorityYear="1812" box="[700,875,306,332]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cayennensis">
<emphasis box="[700,718,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[733,875,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">cayennensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swallen" authorityYear="1966" box="[932,1043,306,332]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis box="[932,950,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[965,1043,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, distinguished mainly by the less pilose inflorescences, resulting in clearly visible spikelets among the trichomes (
<figureCitation box="[1128,1219,345,371]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1840,1861]" captionTargetBox="[159,1406,191,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-152@1.[151,1436,181,1815]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Morphological details of the Eriochrysis species. A. E. cayennensis, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Longhi-Wagner &amp; Welker 10781, ICN). B. E. filiformis, pair of spikelets (Câmara &amp; Filgueiras 30, ICN). C. E. holcoides, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Longhi-Wagner &amp; Welker 10731, ICN). D–G. E. laxa (Welker 489, ICN). D. habit. E. inflorescence. F. pair of spikelets. G. lower glume of the sessile spikelet. H. E. aff. laxa, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 487, ICN). I–J. E. villosa. I. lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 328, ICN). J. lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 182, ICN). K. E. warmingiana, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Filgueiras 1902, ICN). Illustrations by Anelise Scherer and Cassiano A. D. Welker." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5066309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5066309/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
), and the obovate sessile spikelets (
<figureCitation box="[355,482,384,410]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1840,1861]" captionTargetBox="[159,1406,191,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-152@1.[151,1436,181,1815]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Morphological details of the Eriochrysis species. A. E. cayennensis, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Longhi-Wagner &amp; Welker 10781, ICN). B. E. filiformis, pair of spikelets (Câmara &amp; Filgueiras 30, ICN). C. E. holcoides, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Longhi-Wagner &amp; Welker 10731, ICN). D–G. E. laxa (Welker 489, ICN). D. habit. E. inflorescence. F. pair of spikelets. G. lower glume of the sessile spikelet. H. E. aff. laxa, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 487, ICN). I–J. E. villosa. I. lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 328, ICN). J. lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 182, ICN). K. E. warmingiana, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Filgueiras 1902, ICN). Illustrations by Anelise Scherer and Cassiano A. D. Welker." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5066309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5066309/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 1F–G</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beauvois" authorityYear="1812" box="[503,789,384,409]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cayennensis">
<emphasis box="[503,789,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Eriochrysis cayennensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swallen" authorityYear="1966" box="[848,959,384,410]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis box="[848,866,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[881,959,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have densely pilose inflorescences with spikelets hidden among the trichomes, and ovate to elliptic sessile spikelets. Furthermore, the apex of the lower glume is rounded to obtuse in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swallen" authorityYear="1966" box="[587,670,461,487]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laxa">
<emphasis box="[587,605,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[620,670,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">laxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[687,780,461,487]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1840,1861]" captionTargetBox="[159,1406,191,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-152@1.[151,1436,181,1815]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Morphological details of the Eriochrysis species. A. E. cayennensis, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Longhi-Wagner &amp; Welker 10781, ICN). B. E. filiformis, pair of spikelets (Câmara &amp; Filgueiras 30, ICN). C. E. holcoides, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Longhi-Wagner &amp; Welker 10731, ICN). D–G. E. laxa (Welker 489, ICN). D. habit. E. inflorescence. F. pair of spikelets. G. lower glume of the sessile spikelet. H. E. aff. laxa, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 487, ICN). I–J. E. villosa. I. lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 328, ICN). J. lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 182, ICN). K. E. warmingiana, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Filgueiras 1902, ICN). Illustrations by Anelise Scherer and Cassiano A. D. Welker." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5066309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5066309/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 1G</figureCitation>
), but truncate and trilobed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beauvois" authorityYear="1812" box="[1134,1310,461,487]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cayennensis">
<emphasis box="[1134,1152,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1168,1310,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">cayennensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1327,1421,461,487]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1840,1861]" captionTargetBox="[159,1406,191,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-152@1.[151,1436,181,1815]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Morphological details of the Eriochrysis species. A. E. cayennensis, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Longhi-Wagner &amp; Welker 10781, ICN). B. E. filiformis, pair of spikelets (Câmara &amp; Filgueiras 30, ICN). C. E. holcoides, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Longhi-Wagner &amp; Welker 10731, ICN). D–G. E. laxa (Welker 489, ICN). D. habit. E. inflorescence. F. pair of spikelets. G. lower glume of the sessile spikelet. H. E. aff. laxa, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 487, ICN). I–J. E. villosa. I. lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 328, ICN). J. lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 182, ICN). K. E. warmingiana, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Filgueiras 1902, ICN). Illustrations by Anelise Scherer and Cassiano A. D. Welker." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5066309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5066309/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
), and acute to subacute, not lobed (
<figureCitation box="[543,621,500,526]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1840,1861]" captionTargetBox="[159,1406,191,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-152@1.[151,1436,181,1815]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Morphological details of the Eriochrysis species. A. E. cayennensis, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Longhi-Wagner &amp; Welker 10781, ICN). B. E. filiformis, pair of spikelets (Câmara &amp; Filgueiras 30, ICN). C. E. holcoides, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Longhi-Wagner &amp; Welker 10731, ICN). D–G. E. laxa (Welker 489, ICN). D. habit. E. inflorescence. F. pair of spikelets. G. lower glume of the sessile spikelet. H. E. aff. laxa, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 487, ICN). I–J. E. villosa. I. lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 328, ICN). J. lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 182, ICN). K. E. warmingiana, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Filgueiras 1902, ICN). Illustrations by Anelise Scherer and Cassiano A. D. Welker." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5066309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5066309/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 1I</figureCitation>
) or with inconspicuous lobes (
<figureCitation box="[983,1063,500,526]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1840,1861]" captionTargetBox="[159,1406,191,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-152@1.[151,1436,181,1815]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Morphological details of the Eriochrysis species. A. E. cayennensis, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Longhi-Wagner &amp; Welker 10781, ICN). B. E. filiformis, pair of spikelets (Câmara &amp; Filgueiras 30, ICN). C. E. holcoides, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Longhi-Wagner &amp; Welker 10731, ICN). D–G. E. laxa (Welker 489, ICN). D. habit. E. inflorescence. F. pair of spikelets. G. lower glume of the sessile spikelet. H. E. aff. laxa, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 487, ICN). I–J. E. villosa. I. lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 328, ICN). J. lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 182, ICN). K. E. warmingiana, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Filgueiras 1902, ICN). Illustrations by Anelise Scherer and Cassiano A. D. Welker." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5066309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5066309/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 1J</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swallen" authorityYear="1966" box="[1111,1222,500,526]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis box="[1111,1129,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1144,1222,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,306,1106]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuhlmann" authorityYear="1922" baseAuthorityName="Nees" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[198,454,538,563]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="holcoides">
<emphasis box="[198,454,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Eriochrysis holcoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hackel 1883: 254) Kuhlmann (1922: 29)" authorityName="Kuhlmann" authorityPageNumber="29" authorityYear="1922" baseAuthorityName="Hackel" baseAuthorityPageNumber="254" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[513,1205,538,564]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="warmingiana">
<emphasis box="[513,703,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E. warmingiana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hackel, E." box="[719,932,538,564]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="245 - 342" refId="ref1829" refString="Hackel, E. (1883) Gramineae IV., Andropogoneae, Tristegineae. In: Martius, C. F. P. &amp; Eichler, A. G. (eds.) Flora Brasiliensis 2 (3). F. Fleischer, Munich, pp. 245 - 342." type="book chapter" year="1883">Hackel 1883: 254</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Kuhlmann, J. G." box="[949,1205,538,564]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 95" refId="ref1957" refString="Kuhlmann, J. G. (1922) Gramineas. Commissao de Linhas Telegraphicas Estrategicas de Matto Grosso ao Amazonas, Botanica 67: 1 - 95." type="journal article" year="1922">Kuhlmann (1922: 29)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
differ from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swallen" authorityYear="1966" box="[1352,1435,538,564]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laxa">
<emphasis box="[1352,1370,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1385,1435,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">laxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the lanceolate to elliptic sessile spikelets and the lower glume with an acute or acuminate apex (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1840,1861]" captionTargetBox="[159,1406,191,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-152@1.[151,1436,181,1815]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Morphological details of the Eriochrysis species. A. E. cayennensis, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Longhi-Wagner &amp; Welker 10781, ICN). B. E. filiformis, pair of spikelets (Câmara &amp; Filgueiras 30, ICN). C. E. holcoides, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Longhi-Wagner &amp; Welker 10731, ICN). D–G. E. laxa (Welker 489, ICN). D. habit. E. inflorescence. F. pair of spikelets. G. lower glume of the sessile spikelet. H. E. aff. laxa, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 487, ICN). I–J. E. villosa. I. lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 328, ICN). J. lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 182, ICN). K. E. warmingiana, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Filgueiras 1902, ICN). Illustrations by Anelise Scherer and Cassiano A. D. Welker." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5066309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5066309/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 1C, 1K</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hackel 1889: 29) Filgueiras (1997: 231)" authorityName="Filgueiras" authorityPageNumber="231" authorityYear="1997" baseAuthorityName="Hackel" baseAuthorityPageNumber="29" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[215,1007,616,642]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="filiformis">
<emphasis box="[215,482,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Eriochrysis filiformis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hackel, E." box="[499,709,616,642]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 716" refId="ref1884" refString="Hackel, E. (1889) Andropogoneae. In: De Candolle, A. &amp; De Candolle, C. (eds.) Monographiae Phanerogamarum 6. G. Masson, Paris, pp. 1 - 716." type="book chapter" year="1889">Hackel 1889: 29</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Filgueiras, T. S." box="[727,1007,616,642]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="231 - 233" refId="ref1731" refString="Filgueiras, T. S. (1997) A new combination in Eriochrysis (Poaceae: Andropogoneae). Novon 7: 231 - 233." type="journal article" year="1997">Filgueiras (1997: 231)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swallen" authorityYear="1966" box="[1175,1263,616,642]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laxa">
<emphasis box="[1175,1193,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1210,1263,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">laxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the other Brazilian species of the genus by having a pair of spikelets consisting of short- and long-pedicelled spikelets (
<figureCitation box="[160,253,693,719]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1840,1861]" captionTargetBox="[159,1406,191,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-152@1.[151,1436,181,1815]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Morphological details of the Eriochrysis species. A. E. cayennensis, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Longhi-Wagner &amp; Welker 10781, ICN). B. E. filiformis, pair of spikelets (Câmara &amp; Filgueiras 30, ICN). C. E. holcoides, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Longhi-Wagner &amp; Welker 10731, ICN). D–G. E. laxa (Welker 489, ICN). D. habit. E. inflorescence. F. pair of spikelets. G. lower glume of the sessile spikelet. H. E. aff. laxa, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 487, ICN). I–J. E. villosa. I. lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 328, ICN). J. lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 182, ICN). K. E. warmingiana, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Filgueiras 1902, ICN). Illustrations by Anelise Scherer and Cassiano A. D. Welker." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5066309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5066309/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Note that because of this characteristic, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Filgueiras" authorityYear="1997" baseAuthorityName="Hackel" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[760,904,693,719]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="filiformis">
<emphasis box="[760,778,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[794,904,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">filiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was initially erroneously placed in the tribe 
<taxonomicName authority="(Filgueiras 1997)" baseAuthorityName="Filgueiras" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[151,468,732,758]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Paniceae">
Paniceae (
<bibRefCitation author="Filgueiras, T. S." box="[270,459,732,758]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="231 - 233" refId="ref1731" refString="Filgueiras, T. S. (1997) A new combination in Eriochrysis (Poaceae: Andropogoneae). Novon 7: 231 - 233." type="journal article" year="1997">Filgueiras 1997</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Filgueiras" authorityYear="1997" baseAuthorityName="Hackel" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[479,729,732,757]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="filiformis">
<emphasis box="[479,729,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Eriochrysis filiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has narrower leaf blades than the other species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,306,1106]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<bibRefCitation author="Killeen, T. J." box="[198,370,770,796]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="125 - 201" refId="ref1926" refString="Killeen, T. J. (1990) The grasses of Chiquitania, Santa Cruz, Bolivia. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 77: 125 - 201." type="journal article" year="1990">Killeen (1990)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<emphasis box="[499,861,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beauvois" authorityYear="1812" box="[499,634,770,795]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eriochrysis</taxonomicName>
× concepcionensis
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Killeen, T. J." box="[869,1102,770,796]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="125 - 201" refId="ref1926" refString="Killeen, T. J. (1990) The grasses of Chiquitania, Santa Cruz, Bolivia. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 77: 125 - 201." type="journal article" year="1990">Killeen (1990: 157)</bibRefCitation>
as a hybrid between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swallen" authorityYear="1966" box="[1352,1435,770,796]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laxa">
<emphasis box="[1352,1370,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1385,1435,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">laxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beauvois" authorityYear="1812" box="[200,374,809,835]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cayennensis">
<emphasis box="[200,218,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[232,374,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">cayennensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on a single population with intermediate morphology found in 
<collectingRegion box="[1194,1323,809,835]" country="Bolivia" name="Santa Cruz" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Santa Cruz</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1339,1428,809,835]" name="Bolivia" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
) in the same habitat as both parental species. We also found some specimens with intermediate morphology between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swallen" authorityYear="1966" box="[256,339,886,912]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laxa">
<emphasis box="[256,274,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[289,339,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">laxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beauvois" authorityYear="1812" box="[397,572,886,912]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cayennensis">
<emphasis box="[397,415,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[430,572,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">cayennensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a marshland in 
<collectingRegion box="[791,1012,886,912]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1027,1102,886,912]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) together with specimens of the two latter species. These plants, here treated as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swallen" authorityYear="1966" box="[764,897,925,951]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laxa">
<emphasis box="[764,782,925,950]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E</emphasis>
. aff. 
<emphasis box="[846,897,925,950]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">laxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and represented by the specimen 
<emphasis box="[1302,1436,925,950]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Welker 487</emphasis>
(ICN), have obovate sessile spikelets as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swallen" authorityYear="1966" box="[621,704,964,990]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laxa">
<emphasis box="[621,639,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[654,704,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">laxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and densely pilose inflorescences as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beauvois" authorityYear="1812" box="[1140,1313,964,990]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cayennensis">
<emphasis box="[1140,1158,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1172,1313,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">cayennensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The apex of the lower glume is rounded as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swallen" authorityYear="1966" box="[547,630,1002,1028]" class="Insecta" family="Psychidae" genus="Eriochrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laxa">
<emphasis box="[547,565,1002,1027]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[580,630,1002,1027]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">laxa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but has inconspicuous lobes (
<figureCitation box="[993,1086,1002,1028]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1840,1861]" captionTargetBox="[159,1406,191,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-152@1.[151,1436,181,1815]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Morphological details of the Eriochrysis species. A. E. cayennensis, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Longhi-Wagner &amp; Welker 10781, ICN). B. E. filiformis, pair of spikelets (Câmara &amp; Filgueiras 30, ICN). C. E. holcoides, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Longhi-Wagner &amp; Welker 10731, ICN). D–G. E. laxa (Welker 489, ICN). D. habit. E. inflorescence. F. pair of spikelets. G. lower glume of the sessile spikelet. H. E. aff. laxa, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 487, ICN). I–J. E. villosa. I. lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 328, ICN). J. lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Welker 182, ICN). K. E. warmingiana, lower glume of the sessile spikelet (Filgueiras 1902, ICN). Illustrations by Anelise Scherer and Cassiano A. D. Welker." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5066309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5066309/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
). These individuals are likely natural hybrids between these species. We are conducting molecular and cytogenetic studies to examine this issue.
</paragraph>
